  "grammarPoint": {
    "title": "Numbers 1-20, and the noun that follows them",
    "explanation": "The number changes which case the noun takes: **1** (оди́н) + nominative singular (**оди́н день**). **2, 3, 4** + genitive **singular** (**два дня, три дня, четы́ре дня**). **5-20** + genitive **plural** (**пять дней, де́сять дней**).\n\nSame pattern with **час** (hour): **оди́н час, два часа́, пять часо́в**. Learn these two nouns solidly — день and час — and you have the pattern for everything else later.",
    "examples": [
      { "ru": "Оди́н день.", "en": "One day.", "note": "nominative singular" },
      { "ru": "Два дня. Три дня. Четы́ре дня.", "en": "Two/three/four days.", "note": "genitive singular" },
      { "ru": "Пять дней. Де́сять дней.", "en": "Five/ten days.", "note": "genitive plural" },
      { "ru": "Ско́лько мину́т?", "en": "How many minutes?", "note": "same rule works for any counted noun" }
    ]
  },

